From: AWS-LC integration CI <aws-lc-ci@amazon.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Remove BN_FLG_CONSTTIME from SPAKE plugin

AWS-LC does not define BN_FLG_CONSTTIME because all BIGNUM operations
are already constant-time. The BN_set_flags call is a no-op on stock
OpenSSL (which ignores this hint in most contexts) and fails to compile
against AWS-LC. Simply remove it; the constant-time property is
unconditional in AWS-LC.

---
diff --git a/src/plugins/preauth/spake/openssl.c b/src/plugins/preauth/spake/openssl.c
index f2e4b53..81b2f12 100644
--- a/src/plugins/preauth/spake/openssl.c
+++ b/src/plugins/preauth/spake/openssl.c
@@ -150,7 +150,6 @@ unmarshal_w(const groupdata *gdata, const uint8_t *wbytes)
     if (w == NULL)
         return NULL;
 
-    BN_set_flags(w, BN_FLG_CONSTTIME);
 
     if (BN_bin2bn(wbytes, reg->mult_len, w) &&
         BN_div(NULL, w, w, gdata->order, gdata->ctx))
